TO APPLY TO QUESTION #7:  I meant to say ROP instead of EOQ, if i may correct myself.

The factors to consider when deciding when to place an order are the estimated demand during lead time and safety stock.  ROP=EDDLT+Safety stock.  This simply states that an order should be placed at the point where inventory levels = estimated quantity needed to satisfy orders before the next delivery arrives + the z score distribution*standard deviation of the distribution.
